<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 12:49AM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Johnston,
northeastern Bryan, southern Coal, southeastern Pontotoc, Atoka and
southeastern Murray Counties through 145 AM CDT...
At 1249 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles west of Connerville, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Atoka, Tishomingo, Caddo, Bokchito, Ravia, Wapanucka, Lehigh,
Bennington, Mill Creek, Milburn, Tushka, Caney, Kenefic, Bromide,
Clarita, Olney, Fillmore, Reagan, Connerville, and Pontotoc.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
